		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Aug 22nd 1:09 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=96654524932218&num=5&post=1&replyto=96696416712118"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=96696416712118></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=803"><span id=Scholar>GiddyGonzalus</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>155 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.62]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=GiddyGonzalus&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Hmmmm, I've been soloing most of my life. While it is true that you do gain xp faster in a group (just yesterday I was in a group doing Mountain Giants in Frontier and I was the puller, I pulled for 95 mins straight without a rest!), an untactful group is also the fastest way to die (later yesterday I was in a different group with TWO clerics and I had to use my LoH since the clerics were too busy nuking and chatting). But enuf whining .....<br><br>Soloing tactics:<br>Learn when to use your mana and when not to. If your root keeps getting resisted ... stop casting it .. save your mana for heals. <br><br>Bind Wounds. Bind Wounds. Bind Wounds. Bind Wounds. Wish I learned this earlier than I did.<br><br>Use Root wisely. When things r getting too close on the HP, Root then back off and Bind Wounds or Heal (remember your Root may be broken sooner than you want so if it's looking bad for you, use your heal spells).<br><br>Bows. Spend the money to get a decent bow and learn a bit of Fletching to make Class 2 arrows. Why? After you've rooted that critter, backed up and healed yourself, start pumping it full of arrows. Even 6 damage is better than nothing and if you've got a decent enuf bow and arrows you should be doing around 16-20.<br><br>LoH. Use it wisely and sparingly. If the fights real close and you can't Root and back off, don't hesitate to use it. Remember (a group tactic, not a soloing) it is better to LoH a tank than a caster. Why cure 200hp when you can cure up to 1000?! The MOST IMPORTANT thing about LoH: Make sure you've targetted yourself before using it. I've died more times from my own stupidity in targetting than I care to admit.<br><br>My best solo experience was at level 30 in Ill Omen. I was fighting around the Windmill when things got nasty. I wound up battling 6 critters before I had chance to get to safety. It took me over 45min and when I got back I was out of mana, out of bandages, had used my LoH, and I had under 100hp left. I had 2 friends on at the same time doing their own solos. One was a Mage the other a Wizard and both were higher level than I was. Neither one said they would have gotten through 4 or the critters ... when casters go OOM they are sitting ducks. When we Pallys go OOM, the fight is just getting interesting.<br><br>Soloing can be a LOT of fun, but do remember that once you hit higher levels you WILL need a group. Soloing just spices things up for a while.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>________<br><br>I've travelled this world and have seen many wondrous things. You are not one of them.</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >4 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
